1
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:51,584
<i>Yet another quick knockout for
Mason Dixon, almost perfunctory.</i>

2
00:01:51,637 --> 00:01:53,749
<i>The fans let him know
how they feel about it.</i>

3
00:01:53,840 --> 00:01:56,961
<i>Hide the women and children.
This could get ugly.</i>

4
00:01:57,010 --> 00:02:01,318
<i>This crowd does nothing to hide
its anger over this latest debacle.</i>

5
00:02:01,548 --> 00:02:04,504
<i>The fans are mad as hell.
They don't want to take it anymore.</i>

6
00:02:04,585 --> 00:02:07,611
<i>They seem to be blaming Dixon,
a good fighter, for the decline...</i>

7
00:02:07,656 --> 00:02:12,106
<i>... not only of the heavyweight-division
guys, but of the entire sport.</i>

8
00:02:12,095 --> 00:02:13,589
<i>They're actually pelting...</i>

9
00:02:13,695 --> 00:02:17,409
<i>... the undefeated heavyweight
champion of the world with ice.</i>

10
00:02:17,432 --> 00:02:21,289
<i>Maybe this angry, visceral reaction
will pressure Dixon to fight someone...</i>

11
00:02:21,304 --> 00:02:24,366
<i>... who can fight back for a change.
If there's somebody out there.</i>

12
00:02:24,408 --> 00:02:29,866
<i>All of boxing is hoping for a warrior
who thrills us with his passion.</i>

13
00:04:57,749 --> 00:04:59,932
Time goes by too fast.

14
00:05:00,017 --> 00:05:03,423
Yeah? Not fast enough.

15
00:05:03,453 --> 00:05:05,779
- Your kid should've been here.
- That's all right.

16
00:05:05,857 --> 00:05:09,405
- No, it ain't all right.
- The kid gets a little busy sometimes.

17
00:05:09,460 --> 00:05:11,193
He don't get that busy.

18
00:05:11,429 --> 00:05:15,737
Let's not talk about it here, okay?
You're coming tonight, right?

19
00:05:15,769 --> 00:05:19,625
I'm working. I took the tour
the last three years.

20
00:05:19,640 --> 00:05:21,823
I know, but it's the anniversary.

21
00:05:21,908 --> 00:05:23,606
Fine. You got my word.

22
00:05:23,711 --> 00:05:28,363
I appreciate it, thank you.
I owe you, Paulie.

23
00:05:59,752 --> 00:06:03,051
Yo, Robert. What's going on?
Where have you been? You're late.

24
00:06:04,725 --> 00:06:07,501
No. I don't wanna hear this.
Look, your job performance...

25
00:06:07,560 --> 00:06:10,657
...is nowhere near good enough
to be pulling this.

26
00:06:10,696 --> 00:06:13,817
I don't give a damn who your father is.
You understand me?

27
00:06:13,867 --> 00:06:16,229
- All right. Now get out of here.
- Okay.

28
00:06:16,304 --> 00:06:18,108
Thank you, sir.

29
00:06:20,441 --> 00:06:22,803
Yo, Robert. Yo.

30
00:06:22,877 --> 00:06:24,716
- Hey, Rocky.
- Hey.

31
00:06:24,979 --> 00:06:26,224
- Hey, how you doing?
- Hey.

32
00:06:26,349 --> 00:06:27,903
What's up, champ?

33
00:06:28,017 --> 00:06:29,784
- You caught me off guard.
- I know.

34
00:06:29,885 --> 00:06:31,903
I wanted to catch you
before you got busy.

35
00:06:31,988 --> 00:06:33,720
Yeah, it gets busy up there.

36
00:06:33,823 --> 00:06:36,529
- So how you doing? Yeah?
- Real good. Yeah.

37
00:06:36,827 --> 00:06:39,947
- Yo, Rock!
- Yeah, how you doing?

38
00:06:39,995 --> 00:06:41,692
Yeah, real good.

39
00:06:41,798 --> 00:06:44,504
Listen, you wanna go out
and get some coffee?

40
00:06:44,568 --> 00:06:46,336
I'm kind of behind. Maybe later?

41
00:06:46,771 --> 00:06:49,963
Yeah. That'd be great. You ought to
come by the restaurant tonight.

42
00:06:50,007 --> 00:06:52,545
I can have something
made special for you.

43
00:06:52,612 --> 00:06:56,681
Tonight I can't. I got plans.
A few of the guys get together.

44
00:06:57,082 --> 00:06:59,859
- Did I do something wrong?
- What do you mean?

45
00:06:59,920 --> 00:07:02,731
Well, I don't know exactly
what I mean...

46
00:07:02,789 --> 00:07:06,894
...but I just think, like, when I come
here, you don't feel so comfortable.

47
00:07:06,927 --> 00:07:09,289
And I certainly don't wanna do that.

48
00:07:10,564 --> 00:07:13,721
- Well, you throw a big shadow.
- A big shadow?

49
00:07:13,768 --> 00:07:16,509
You're not gonna get anything done
down here, Robert.

50
00:07:16,571 --> 00:07:20,084
Well, if you're not gonna introduce me,
I will. Hi, I'm William Tomilson.

51
00:07:20,109 --> 00:07:22,398
- How you doing?
- Your son works for me.

52
00:07:22,845 --> 00:07:24,614
- It's a good job.
- Yeah.

53
00:07:24,714 --> 00:07:27,669
I've told Robert about 20 times
that I wanted to meet you.

54
00:07:27,717 --> 00:07:29,971
You're pretty busy,
which isn't a bad thing.

55
00:07:30,088 --> 00:07:32,556
- I get a little tied up.
- Grab a shot, will you?

56
00:07:33,055 --> 00:07:36,426
I may not get this chance again.
Old warhorses have to stick together.

57
00:07:36,460 --> 00:07:38,892
- The old horses, yeah.
- I'll tell you.

58
00:07:39,665 --> 00:07:42,856
- Good thing it's not your left.
- This makes you popular with people.

59
00:07:43,134 --> 00:07:46,196
- One, two, three.
- Finally, we get to meet.

60
00:07:46,237 --> 00:07:49,084
I gotta get going. It was nice
to meet you face to face.

61
00:07:49,142 --> 00:07:52,654
You take care of yourself.
Robert, I'll see you later.

62
00:07:54,915 --> 00:07:58,629
I gotta get going.
I'll change my plans for tonight.

63
00:07:58,652 --> 00:08:00,598
That'd be great.
I'm looking forward to it.

64
00:08:00,688 --> 00:08:02,183
- How you doing?
- Okay.

65
00:08:02,289 --> 00:08:04,164
- Okay.
- All right.

66
00:08:04,259 --> 00:08:07,807
And do not let those numbers
drive you crazy.

67
00:08:07,829 --> 00:08:12,065
- Too late.
- Use an eraser, get rid of all of them.

68
00:08:14,004 --> 00:08:15,284
- Yo, Rock.
- Hey, guys.

69
00:08:15,605 --> 00:08:17,752
- Hey, Rock.
- Hey, how you doing?

70
00:08:33,123 --> 00:08:34,155
There you go.

71
00:08:39,798 --> 00:08:43,405
It'll be about 10 tenths.
You guys take care, okay? You got it.

72
00:08:46,573 --> 00:08:48,685
I'll try a few of these later on.

73
00:08:49,442 --> 00:08:52,076
- It's good for baking.
- How much...?

74
00:08:52,146 --> 00:08:54,199
- Yo, Paul, what's the cost?
- 58.40, sir.

75
00:08:54,281 --> 00:08:56,785
All right, take it out of that.
I trust you.

76
00:08:58,987 --> 00:09:00,754
- How you doing?
- You're too generous.

77
00:09:00,856 --> 00:09:02,659
Not a problem.

78
00:09:18,708 --> 00:09:21,247
How you guys doing?

79
00:09:27,486 --> 00:09:29,670
How we doing, Isabel?

80
00:09:29,754 --> 00:09:32,257
Okay, except for the freebie
reading the Bible.

81
00:09:32,325 --> 00:09:34,864
- He's okay.
- Just because you fought him...

82
00:09:34,928 --> 00:09:37,954
...don't mean you gotta feed him.
He doesn't look like a fighter.

83
00:09:37,999 --> 00:09:39,731
Spider Rico could hit.

84
00:09:39,832 --> 00:09:42,503
- Listen, how's your stomach?
- It's okay.

85
00:09:42,604 --> 00:09:45,000
If you keep rubbing olive oil
on your stomach...

86
00:09:45,073 --> 00:09:47,150
...your kid's gonna be
born very strong.

87
00:09:47,241 --> 00:09:50,232
- Okay, Rocky. Whatever you say.
- No, really.

88
00:09:52,981 --> 00:09:55,687
- Yo, how you doing, Spider?
- God bless you, Rocky.

89
00:09:55,784 --> 00:09:57,065
Thanks.

90
00:10:02,325 --> 00:10:04,402
How you guys doing?

91
00:10:06,162 --> 00:10:10,162
Jose, can you make something special
for my kid who's coming tonight?

92
00:10:10,200 --> 00:10:11,517
No problemo.

93
00:10:11,636 --> 00:10:14,863
Good. I appreciate it.

94
00:10:16,475 --> 00:10:19,536
<i>Back and forth, back and forth,
give and take.</i>

95
00:10:19,579 --> 00:10:22,984
And then I went in there like an animal
and threw him into the corner...

96
00:10:23,015 --> 00:10:26,872
...and I unloaded everything I had.
Hook, hook, hook, left, left, left.

97
00:10:26,886 --> 00:10:29,627
But Creed, he kept
busting me back pretty good...

98
00:10:29,690 --> 00:10:31,707
...and the agony began to pile up.

99
00:10:31,791 --> 00:10:35,233
Then I heard the best sound
that I ever heard in my life...

100
00:10:35,262 --> 00:10:36,959
- The bell.
- That's right, the bell.

101
00:10:37,064 --> 00:10:40,364
I ain't never been so tired,
and I'm sitting in my corner.

102
00:10:40,401 --> 00:10:43,142
I'm trying to figure out
how to survive the last round...

103
00:10:43,204 --> 00:10:45,114
...when Mickey leans
into my ear and says:

104
00:10:45,206 --> 00:10:48,434
"Come on, get out there
and fight this guy hard, you bum.

105
00:10:48,477 --> 00:10:53,520
You gotta be first. You gotta be first."
I said, "Yo, Mick, if I could...

106
00:10:53,482 --> 00:10:56,366
- "I would."
...I would."

107
00:10:56,420 --> 00:10:57,773
The end.

108
00:11:24,453 --> 00:11:27,787
<i>Yet another quick knockout for
Mason Dixon, almost perfunctory.</i>

109
00:11:27,822 --> 00:11:30,599
<i>The fans let him know
how they feel about it.</i>

110
00:11:30,659 --> 00:11:32,320
<i>They're actually pelting...</i>

111
00:11:32,426 --> 00:11:37,219
<i>... the undefeated heavyweight
champion of the world with ice.</i>

112
00:11:42,071 --> 00:11:45,512
Hello, Adrian's. Yeah?

113
00:11:45,908 --> 00:11:50,428
Tell him you can't make it?
Yeah, I'll give him the message.

114
00:11:51,649 --> 00:11:55,957
I just kept hearing Mickey's voice
in my head over and over again.

115
00:11:55,987 --> 00:11:57,969
I just dug down,
and before you know it...

116
00:11:58,056 --> 00:12:01,390
...it was toe to toe and it was...
Excuse me.

117
00:12:01,425 --> 00:12:05,840
Your son said he can't make it.
He said he'll take a rain check. Okay?

118
00:12:19,081 --> 00:12:20,326
<i>Look at these birds.</i>

119
00:12:20,448 --> 00:12:23,367
<i>Don't these birds look like candy?
Flying candy?</i>

120
00:12:23,417 --> 00:12:25,399
<i>Hey, birdie,
you wanna fly me home?</i>

121
00:12:25,486 --> 00:12:28,119
You need somebody
to walk you home?

122
00:12:28,957 --> 00:12:29,989
<i>No?</i>

123
00:12:30,124 --> 00:12:35,239
It's a cold night. We need a few laughs
in our life. What do you think? Maybe?

124
00:12:35,698 --> 00:12:37,775
<i>Maybe? Maybe?</i>

125
00:12:37,868 --> 00:12:40,467
<i>Okay. Let's get out of here, okay?</i>

126
00:12:55,355 --> 00:12:57,894
That place ain't changed much
from last year.

127
00:12:57,956 --> 00:12:59,796
Are we done?

128
00:13:00,026 --> 00:13:02,316
Hey, how you doing, Mick?

129
00:13:05,097 --> 00:13:07,150
That sign is falling apart, Paulie.

130
00:13:07,233 --> 00:13:10,710
The whole world is falling apart.
Look at us.

131
00:13:10,737 --> 00:13:13,206
Don't talk crazy, Paulie.

132
00:13:13,341 --> 00:13:18,835
You know, I think if you live someplace
long enough, you are that place.

133
00:13:19,214 --> 00:13:21,885
I ain't no talking building.

134
00:13:21,951 --> 00:13:24,312
Come on, it's getting late, Rocko.

135
00:13:24,521 --> 00:13:27,368
I get a headache from this train.

136
00:13:47,179 --> 00:13:50,170
I remember when
she was standing there...

137
00:13:50,216 --> 00:13:54,072
...all nervous and shy,
with this little smile.

138
00:13:54,553 --> 00:13:57,889
And all I wanted her to do
was trust me.

139
00:14:01,096 --> 00:14:03,149
She did.

140
00:14:04,132 --> 00:14:06,671
- She did.
- You done?

141
00:14:22,120 --> 00:14:25,038
- How long are we staying here?
- Not long.

142
00:14:25,088 --> 00:14:27,556
Well, I'm glad they tore
this ice rink down.

143
00:14:27,626 --> 00:14:28,907
Come on.

144
00:14:29,027 --> 00:14:32,991
You heard me.
I'm happy they tore it apart.

145
00:14:36,468 --> 00:14:41,120
First time I walked your sister
across this ice, we was over there.

146
00:14:41,106 --> 00:14:44,750
She was nervous, but I wasn't so great
on the blades either.

147
00:14:44,778 --> 00:14:48,978
Ice is stupid. People standing on ice
are more stupid.

148
00:14:50,052 --> 00:14:54,181
And over there,
when she was falling...

149
00:14:54,354 --> 00:14:55,884
...and my hand grabbed her...

150
00:14:56,958 --> 00:15:00,993
...and I got her arm through that coat,
I could feel it.

151
00:15:01,630 --> 00:15:03,470
Electric.

152
00:15:03,900 --> 00:15:06,439
You said the same thing
last year, Rock.

153
00:15:07,637 --> 00:15:08,954
Did I?

154
00:15:09,072 --> 00:15:11,362
- so you better develop your brain.

155
00:15:11,441 --> 00:15:13,386
- You're left-handed.
- Absolutely.

156
00:15:13,477 --> 00:15:15,874
Come on, Rock. Let's go.

157
00:15:18,216 --> 00:15:22,179
We're done. There's no place
to sit down around here.

158
00:15:22,187 --> 00:15:23,540
It's all right.

159
00:15:23,655 --> 00:15:28,176
It ain't all right! It's depressing
and freaking cold!

160
00:15:28,727 --> 00:15:30,424
What's the matter with you, Paulie?

161
00:15:30,729 --> 00:15:32,912
You're living backwards, Rocko!

162
00:15:32,998 --> 00:15:36,641
Change the channel from yesterday!
Yesterday wasn't so great!

163
00:15:36,669 --> 00:15:39,172
- It was to me.
- Not to me!

164
00:15:40,941 --> 00:15:44,240
You treated her good.
You had the good times.

165
00:15:45,013 --> 00:15:48,692
I treated her bad.
I don't have to think about this.

166
00:15:49,952 --> 00:15:52,207
She always loved you, Paulie.

167
00:15:56,427 --> 00:15:59,832
Sorry, Rocko,
I can't do this no more.

168
00:17:12,545 --> 00:17:13,754
Can I help you?

169
00:17:14,113 --> 00:17:16,890
No, no, I used to come down
to this place a long time ago.

170
00:17:16,949 --> 00:17:19,690
I was just looking around.
No big deal.

171
00:17:20,453 --> 00:17:21,733
Can I get you a drink?

172
00:17:23,623 --> 00:17:27,100
- All right. Maybe just a short beer.
- Okay.

173
00:17:35,872 --> 00:17:37,746
Go. Go on.

174
00:17:38,640 --> 00:17:40,550
Yeah, go on.
Get him to buy a round.

175
00:17:40,642 --> 00:17:42,624
Get him to buy a round. Go.

176
00:17:42,912 --> 00:17:45,902
Get him to... He's got it.
He's spending money.

177
00:17:45,949 --> 00:17:51,372
Listen, I don't mean to cross the line
or anything...

178
00:17:51,321 --> 00:17:54,442
...but I read about your wife's passing
a few years back.

179
00:17:54,491 --> 00:17:56,116
Yeah, it was woman cancer.

180
00:17:56,227 --> 00:17:59,323
Yeah. I always heard
she was a nice person.

181
00:17:59,364 --> 00:18:01,903
Yeah, the best.

182
00:18:02,835 --> 00:18:05,303
- Do I know you?
- We met a long time ago.

183
00:18:05,704 --> 00:18:06,807
We did?

184
00:18:06,973 --> 00:18:09,571
When I was a kid,
you walked me home.

185
00:18:09,642 --> 00:18:13,048
- I did?
- Told me to stop smoking and things.

186
00:18:14,449 --> 00:18:16,738
Stop smoking...

187
00:18:17,317 --> 00:18:20,996
Are you Little Marie that used to
hang out at that Atomic Hoagie shop?

188
00:18:21,023 --> 00:18:22,932
Yeah, that's right.

189
00:18:23,491 --> 00:18:25,959
Yeah, now I remember.
I walked you home.

190
00:18:26,028 --> 00:18:30,063
When you got there, you turned
around and said, "Screw you, creepo."

191
00:18:30,065 --> 00:18:32,498
- I didn't say that.
- Yeah, you did.

192
00:18:32,569 --> 00:18:36,153
- You sure?
- Great insults last a long time.

193
00:18:36,172 --> 00:18:39,684
Yo! Yo, is that you?
Is that really you?

194
00:18:40,077 --> 00:18:42,509
- How you doing?
- I think he wants to drink alone.

195
00:18:42,647 --> 00:18:45,744
Well, then give him his drink, then.
I ain't stopping you.

196
00:18:45,817 --> 00:18:49,401
What's that, your man or something?
No, I don't think so.

197
00:18:52,091 --> 00:18:55,568
Anyway, me and my friends,
we're right down there.

198
00:18:55,595 --> 00:18:59,035
Think you could buy us a round?
You got the money. Just one round.

199
00:18:59,065 --> 00:19:02,091
Hey. Thank you.

200
00:19:02,133 --> 00:19:05,361
What are you doing
pushing my hand away like that?

201
00:19:05,406 --> 00:19:07,910
- What's your name?
- Angie. What do you wanna know for?

202
00:19:07,975 --> 00:19:11,072
- Don't be playing a fool for that guy.
- A fool?

203
00:19:11,113 --> 00:19:12,358
- Yeah.
- A fool?

204
00:19:12,480 --> 00:19:15,577
I'm the fool? You're the fool, not me!

205
00:19:15,618 --> 00:19:18,775
You got it twisted. You're the fool.
I'm a person, just like you.

206
00:19:18,854 --> 00:19:22,568
You ain't no better than me. You think
you're a big shot now? You're nothing.

207
00:19:22,591 --> 00:19:26,590
You ain't no better than me.
No better!

208
00:19:28,064 --> 00:19:29,417
Glad you dropped in?

209
00:19:29,533 --> 00:19:32,309
I think the neighborhood
is changing a little.

210
00:19:33,069 --> 00:19:35,917
- What was that all about?
- I don't know. Forget about it.

211
00:19:35,973 --> 00:19:39,343
I'm gonna lock up, so if you wanna
take off, I'll tally everything up.

212
00:19:39,379 --> 00:19:41,076
- Yeah, thanks.
- How you doing, Rock?

213
00:19:41,179 --> 00:19:42,839
I'm good, thanks.

214
00:19:45,317 --> 00:19:48,272
- You live around here?
- About eight blocks from here.

215
00:19:49,321 --> 00:19:51,231
Eight blocks.

216
00:19:52,325 --> 00:19:54,164
You need a lift?

217
00:19:54,559 --> 00:19:56,672
All right.

218
00:19:56,763 --> 00:19:58,638
Did you ever get married?

219
00:19:58,732 --> 00:20:00,607
- Yeah, sort of.
- Sort of?

220
00:20:00,701 --> 00:20:03,300
- Yeah, well, he took off.
- Poof, just like that?

221
00:20:03,370 --> 00:20:05,590
Yeah, just like that.

222
00:20:05,941 --> 00:20:08,931
- You sort of have any kids?
- Yeah, I got one kid.

223
00:20:09,010 --> 00:20:12,796
Yeah? Me too. Me too.
Wonderful boy.

224
00:20:12,815 --> 00:20:16,636
Hey, tough guy! What's the matter,
you can't buy a round?

225
00:20:16,652 --> 00:20:19,322
The girl was being nice
to your dumb ass.

226
00:20:19,388 --> 00:20:22,165
- What you doing with that pig?
- Think you can disrespect us?

227
00:20:22,226 --> 00:20:25,252
- She ain't nothing but a jealous bitch!
- Come on back!

228
00:20:25,495 --> 00:20:27,335
Hey, don't listen to them.

229
00:20:27,432 --> 00:20:30,588
Both of youse,
you ain't no better than me.

